SIMPLE: reinsure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reinsure
<hw>Re`in*sure"</hw> <pr>(-sh?r")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To insure again after a former insurance has ceased; to renew
insurance on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To insure, as life or property, in favor of one who
has taken an insurance risk upon it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The insurer may cause the property insured to be
<qex>reinsured</qex> by other persons.</q>
<rj><qau>Walsh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reinsurer</ent>⟦br⟧
